<h2 style=3D"font-weight:bold;font-family:&quot;Arial Black&quot;,Arial,Hel=
vetica,sans-serif;letter-spacing:-1px;font-size:20px;border-bottom-width:1p=
x;border-bottom-style:dotted;margin:0px;padding:16px 0px 5px">Working from =
home</h2><p style=3D"margin:16px 0">I mean the basic situation in investmen=
t banking is that if you are a junior analyst and you are in the office few=
er than like 80 hours a week, you will be in trouble, while if you are a se=
nior managing director and you=E2=80=99re in the office more than like 20 h=
ours a week you will be in trouble. Analysts are expected to show up by 10i=
sh, look busy and be available for eight hours, order dinner, and then sett=
le in=C2=A0for a long night of building models and turning pitchbooks. If y=
ou=E2=80=99re not around and available all day, and cranking on Excel all n=
ight, you are not doing your job.</p><p style=3D"margin:16px 0">MDs, meanwh=
ile, are expected to get on planes and go meet with clients to win new busi=
ness. Of course=C2=A0sometimes they need to be in the office to supervise a=
nd motivate their underlings, to tell them what pages they want in the pitc=
hbook, etc. Other times they will do client meetings by telephone or videoc=
onference; it happens. But in general if you are sitting around your office=
 all day, instead of your clients=E2=80=99 offices, you are not doing the h=
ighest-value-add part of your job.</p><p style=3D"margin:16px 0">Obviously =
this was upended by the pandemic. But in different ways. Analysts lost a lo=
t of learning and mentorship and social opportunities: Instead of hanging o=
ut with other 23-year-olds and learning Excel shortcuts and financial-model=
ing techniques and where to find the good pitchbook pages, they had to mudd=
le through their work on their own, which took longer and was less satisfyi=
ng. Instead of sitting in the MD=E2=80=99s office to listen to client calls=
, with the MD occasionally muting her line to explain what was going on, th=
ey churned out pitchbooks alone at home. Instead of ordering dinner to the =
office and joking around with their friends, they ate dinner at home while =
working quietly and sadly. Sure they didn=E2=80=99t have to commute, but th=
eir commute from Murray Hill wasn=E2=80=99t that long anyway, and their apa=
rtments aren=E2=80=99t=C2=A0that nice. Perhaps they have moved back in with=
 their parents, which is a decidedly mixed bag.</p><p style=3D"margin:16px =
0">Meanwhile the MDs, freed from the need to commute to the office, can wor=
k from their much nicer Hamptons houses. They don=E2=80=99t need to get on =
planes four times a week to meet with clients; they can just do everything =
from home and then go to the beach. Perhaps they are learning less from the=
 serendipity and in-person interactions of being in the office, but they we=
re pretty far up the learning curve already. Also, remember, they just were=
n=E2=80=99t in the office that much to begin with; they were always on plan=
es to meet with clients so the serendipity was limited.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in:16px 0">Now the pandemic measures are ending and banks are going back to=
 work. If you are a junior banker that=E2=80=99s mostly good; you can see y=
our friends and learn stuff and not work out of your bedroom. If you are a =
senior banker that means getting back on planes and going to see clients, w=
hich is exhausting, but also frankly if you=E2=80=99ve made it to a senior =
job at an investment bank that =E2=80=94=C2=A0the social aspects of the job=
, meeting with potential clients and trying to befriend them and understand=
 their business in person =E2=80=94=C2=A0is probably something you enjoy. B=
ut when you get back from a client trip late Tuesday night, and you=E2=80=
=99ve got another trip planned Thursday morning, and the bank wants you bac=
k in the office on Wednesday to sit at your desk =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em>that=C2=
=A0</em>feels=C2=A0unnecessary now, doesn=E2=80=99t it? If you=E2=80=99ve g=
ot a day between trips to catch up on emails and phone calls, you=E2=80=99d=
 rather spend it at your Hamptons house than schlepping into the office.</p=
><p style=3D"margin:16px 0"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/24372120.265775/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9qcG1vcmdhb=
i1nb2xkbWFuLWNhbGwtdGltZS1vbi13b3JrLWZyb20taG9tZS10aGVpci1yaXZhbHMtYXJlLXJl=
YWR5LXRvLXBvdW5jZS0xMTYyNTU2MzgwMD9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3M2/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cBb894d3da" style=3D"color:#000000;text-decoration:none!important;bord=
er-bottom-width:1px;border-bottom-color:#000000;border-bottom-style:solid;b=
ackground-color:#ccc" target=3D"_blank">Anyway</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin:16px 0">There is a growing divide on Wall Street: firms calling =
employees back and firms telling people they can work from home.</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin:16px 0">Titans like Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and JPMorgan Chase=
 &amp; Co. are taking a hard-line approach, beefing up in-person staff five=
 days a week in New York even though it might mean losing talent. Rivals in=
cluding Citigroup Inc. are touting flexibility, betting that a softer appro=
ach will help them poach top traders and deal makers. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=
=3D"margin:16px 0">Culture is at the heart of the debate. Some say the trad=
ing floor is the last bastion of Wall Street, where interns and young emplo=
yees learn by osmosis. Others think record results in a remote-work year pr=
ove that the trading floor and the office alike have lost their relevance.<=
/p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin:16px 0">My model is that, in the short t=
erm, more work-from-home is probably the good trade: =E2=80=9CRecord result=
s in a remote-work year=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>prove that you can d=
o it successfully for a time, using primarily bankers and traders whom you=
=E2=80=99ve already trained and acculturated in the office.[2] And senior b=
ankers and traders=C2=A0<em>will=C2=A0</em>prefer to work from their Hampto=
ns houses, so you can keep your senior bankers and poach your competitors=
=E2=80=99 if you=E2=80=99re more flexible.=C2=A0But in the long run you wan=
t your junior bankers and traders to be trained, at the office, by the seni=
or bankers and traders, and it=E2=80=99s hard to do that if all of the seni=
or people are at home all the time.=C2=A0</p><h2 style=3D"font-weight:bold;=
